# Accessibility Guidelines

## WCAG Compliance
- Follow WCAG 2.1 AA standards
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Implement keyboard navigation
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Screen Reader Support
```typescript
// Good: Proper ARIA labels and roles
<button
  aria-label="Flip flashcard to see definition"
  aria-expanded={isFlipped}
  onClick={handleFlip}
>
  <span className="sr-only">
    {isFlipped ? 'Show word' : 'Show definition'}
  </span>
  {isFlipped ? <EyeIcon /> : <EyeOffIcon />}
</button>
```

## Keyboard Navigation
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Implement proper tab order
- Use focus management for modals and dropdowns
- Provide visible focus indicators

## Form Accessibility
- Use proper form labels and associations
- Implement field validation with clear error messages
- Use fieldset and legend for grouped inputs
- Provide helpful instructions and examples

## Vietnamese Language Considerations
- Ensure proper text direction support
- Use appropriate fonts for Vietnamese characters
- Test with Vietnamese screen readers
- Consider cultural accessibility needs

## Testing Accessibility
- Use automated accessibility testing tools
- Test with keyboard-only navigation
- Test with screen readers
- Validate color contrast ratios
- Test with different zoom levels